  <description><![CDATA[<p>Ulvik is a picturesque village that's on a sheltered bay of the Hardangerfjord, with its wooden houses against a scenic mountain backdrop. The village is also known as the Orchard of <a data-udi="umb://document/286d71b6bae94f84a7ac63448c015f54" href="/{localLink:umb://document/286d71b6bae94f84a7ac63448c015f54}" title="Norway">Norway</a> which, of course, is because o the amount of fruit trees, You'll be able to try some of the delicious fresh products when visiting one of the many local farms. </p>
<p>There's a network of walking paths, some through the wild flow meadows, so this village is great for walkers. As well as walking there's cycling, boating and fishing in Ulvik, but your favourite part will be the scenery reflecting into the crystal clear water.</p>]]></description>
